  "prompt": "What should happen to our internet accounts, like Emails and Facebook, when we die?",
  "response": "This is an increasingly important issue in the digital age. Different platforms have different policies:\n\n1. Google: Offers an \"Inactive Account Manager\" where you can choose to have your data deleted or shared with specific contacts after a period of inactivity.\n\n2. Facebook: Allows you to designate a \"legacy contact\" who can manage your memorial account after your death, or choose to have your account permanently deleted.\n\n3. Many email providers allow account deletion or memorialization through their terms of service.\n\nSome recommended steps include:\n- Creating a digital will\n- Leaving instructions for digital account management\n- Using password managers that can be accessed by trusted contacts\n- Informing trusted family members about your digital accounts\n\nUltimately, it's wise to plan ahead and specify what you want to happen to your digital accounts after your death.",
